##this is a professional instruction on how to use the sha256 hash function
##this is very professional
##plz tell me via wechat if there is anything problematic

To:
sha_256 hash a $#size_t#$ type data: text
Do in C code:
    
    BYTE buf[sha_256_BLOCK_SIZE]; //buff to hold the hash
	sha_256_CTX ctx;              //the ctx
	sha_256_init(&ctx);           //initiating the ctx
	sha_256_update(&ctx, text, strlen(text)); //hashing
	sha_256_final(&ctx, buf);     //recieving the hash

        After:
         build up a shared library with: sha_256.c, sha_256.h; called: sha_256.so
         link sha_256.so with your code; To:
          use: $#typedef struct#$ BYTE, $#typedef struct#$ sha_256_CTX; def-from: sha_256.h
          
        retfA
oDoT
